# Linux Server Won't Boot

> Troubleshooting Track — Exercise 02

> **A Linux server that will not boot is one of the most stressful incidents an engineer can face.**
>
> The system is down.
>
> SSH is unavailable.
>
> Monitoring may be offline.
>
> Customers may be impacted.
>
> Your job is to systematically determine where the boot process failed and recover safely.

---

# Why This Exercise Exists

Many engineers know how to troubleshoot:

```text
Running Systems
```

Few know how to troubleshoot:

```text
Systems That Never Start
```

A server that fails during boot is different because:

```text
No SSH

No Applications

No Kubernetes

No Docker

No Monitoring Agents
```

You lose most of your normal troubleshooting tools.

Understanding boot failures requires understanding Linux startup from first principles.

---

# The Problem This Exercise Solves

Imagine receiving an alert:

```text
Production API Offline

Server Unreachable

No SSH Access

Monitoring Agent Down
```

Questions immediately appear:

```text
Is Hardware Dead?

