# Mental Model

Think of Linux booting like launching a rocket.

```text
Power

↓

Firmware

↓

Bootloader

↓

Kernel

↓

Init System

↓

Services

↓

Applications
```

Failure at any stage prevents reaching orbit.

---

# First Principles

A Linux system does not magically start.

Booting is a sequence of dependencies.

```mermaid
flowchart TD

Power_On

--> Firmware

--> Bootloader

--> Kernel

--> Init_System

--> Services

--> Login
```

Each stage depends on the previous stage.

---

# Critical Insight

Most boot failures occur because:

```text
A Dependency Failed
```

Examples:

```text
Missing Disk

Corrupt Filesystem

Broken Kernel

Invalid Configuration

Failed Mount

Failed systemd Unit
```

